136,http://www.armslist.com/posts/4983136,For Sale:  M39 Finnish Mosin Nagant VKT,"Livonia, Detroit, Michigan",$ 450,"Listed On: Wednesday, December 23, 2015",Rifles,no type,7.62x54R                                                                                ,Bolt Action                                                                                ,Rifle,"For sale:
Numbers matching 1944 Finnish Mosin Nagant VKT(Valmet) Manufacture.

Beautiful rifle, no rust, cosmoline free, well oiled, smooth bolt, very accurate. The rifling is very strong and the bore is in great condition, I will send you a picture of the bore upon your request.

This rifle has a VKT barrel, which is regarded as a nearly match grade quality barrel, my groups at 100 yards with this rifle can attest to that. This rifle also bears AZF markings on the receiver, indicating that the receiver was originally Austrio-hungarian. A true collectors piece, yet a highly accurate and reliable firearm.
The M39 was the Finnish rendition of the Mosin Nagant in WWII. The Finns kept the hex receiver, magazine and bolt from a Russian model 91 Mosin and replaced everything else.

The Finn upgrades included: a heavier stock, new heavier barrel bands, upgraded sights, crisp two stage trigger, a cleaning rod unique to the M39 and the ability to mount a sling under the rifle in a traditional manner or on the side in a cavalry/ski troop method.
I am in the metro Detroit area and I am willing to meet at a convenient place for both of us. Asking $450 or best offer. I am willing to ship to you."
